Dan Negrey

Hello, world!

My name is Dan Negrey, and I am a Data Scientist based in Cleveland, OH. I am passionate about statistical computing, data visualization, machine learning and reproducible research. I strive to utilize best practices throughout my work which includes promoting and teaching these techniques to others.

Latest news

  • March 4, 2017: new project - Data Days CLE 2017: Introducing R
  • May 15, 2016: blog post - Leaflet by Example: Election 2000
  • April 4, 2016: new site launched, built using R Markdown!

A little bit about the site…

This is the central hub for my professional portfolio. My goal is that visitors gain an understanding about data science through a variety of resources, learn about the projects on which I am working, enjoy some interesting blog posts and get to know a little more about me.

Technology approach

I consider myself “technology agnostic”. Fortunately, the nature of my work lends itself to using a variety of tools. I generally prefer open-source technologies and as my work greatly emphasizes analytics and visualization, I am a very enthusiastic R user! I use git for version control and honestly don’t know how I ever lived without it (I refer to this earlier period in my life as “b.g.” - before git).
